	(text "difference op-amp\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 366.014 265.684 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "29ffc5b5-3cab-4073-80b2-037787cf3d7a")
	)
	(text "Depends on the contactor:\n1. C7- needed\n2. Gigavac- not needed"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 68.58 240.538 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "5be0055b-9fc3-45aa-86f7-5cfabb2be41e")
	)
	(text "====================================================================\nHV PRECHARGE SENSING & HARDWARE THRESHOLD CIRCUIT\n\nOverview:\nThis circuit safely steps down, isolates, and monitors the High Voltage (HV) traction bus. It provides both a continuous analog telemetry signal and a hardware-level digital trigger to the MCU for executing the Make-Before-Break precharge contactor sequence.\n\nStage 1: HV Attenuation\nA 1MΩ / 5kΩ resistive voltage divider reduces the raw HV pack voltage down to a safe, measurable low-voltage range suitable for the isolation amplifier.\n\nStage 2: Galvanic Isolation (ISO224)\nThe stepped-down HV signal passes through an ISO224 precision isolation amplifier. This safely bridges the high-voltage and low-voltage domains, outputting a proportional differential signal while protecting the low-voltage control electronics from deadly potentials.\n\nStage 3: Differential to Single-Ended Conversion\nAn operational amplifier (U2) configured as a difference amplifier converts the ISO224's differential output into a clean, single-ended, ground-referenced analog voltage (HV_SENSE_SAFE).\n\nStage 4: Hardware Schmitt Trigger (LM393)\nA dedicated voltage comparator (U3A) monitors HV_SENSE_SAFE against an adjustable reference voltage set by trimmer RV1.\n\nRV1 is tuned to represent 95% of the maximum HV pack voltage.\n\nR13 (100kΩ) provides positive feedback (hysteresis) to prevent signal chatter.\n\nWhen the bus reaches 95%, the open-collector output releases, allowing an external 3.3V pull-up resistor to snap the STM32 input line HIGH. This hardware trigger commands the MCU to immediately close the Main AIR and subsequently open the Precharge relay.\n\nNote: Unused comparator inputs (U3B) are tied to GND to prevent parasitic oscillation from EV powertrain EMI."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 38.862 355.346 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "94284e54-0678-4f89-a16e-d00d3be59e00")
	)
	(text "isolation amplifier\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 298.45 254.762 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "a6a5bd90-4d07-4a0d-9f8b-3085c5cb881a")
	)
